snippet.textDisplay:
It’s based on TS Eliot’s Old Possum’s Book of Practical Cat’s which is a collection of poems about cats. The stage play is odd in and of itself, but the technical ability of the actors made it work. It was the longest running show on Broadway for a time. Why they thought it would translate to film is beyond me.
Fun fact: they spent thousands of dollars on condoms because this was before modern headset microphones and they had to wear the mics on their bodies. They’d get so sweaty during the performance that they’d cover the mic with a condom to keep it intact.
